Description: Shoulder sherd of large North Ionian pottery krater or dinos; exterior, cream slip; thick painted black band with added red and white lines; above, frieze containing spirals and dot in black; inscription cut on black band.
Curator's comments: The sherd makes a touch join with 1886,0401.946.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GG.1199)
